[Done] Step 1: Install the Office 365 Moodle Plugin

[Permissions] Step 2: Configure the connection between the Office 365 plugin and Azure Active Directory

	Permissions manquantes :
    Have full access to user calendars
    Read and write directory data
    Have full access to user files
    Read and write all groups
    Read and write all OneNote notebooks that user can access
    Read items in all site collections
    Read and write all users' full profiles

Documentation:
https://docs.moodle.org/34/en/Office365#Configure_your_Application_Permissions

[Pending] Step 3: Deploy the Moodle Assistant Bot to Azure

3.1 Create a new bot application
	Accédez à la section Inscriptions d'applications du portail Azure et enregistrez une nouvelle application. Entrez l'ID de l'application et le secret client ci-dessous : 
	https://aka.ms/MoodleBotRegistration

	Champs manquantes :
	bot_app_id
	bot_app_password
	
3.2 Deploy to Azure (provisioning MoodleBot assistant)
	https://aka.ms/DeployMoodleTeamsBot
	Champs manquantes :
	bot_sharedsecret
	bot_webhook_endpoint

[Pending] 3.3 Download manifest file

Step 4: Deploy your Microsoft Teams app
	Upload a custom app

